CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 11, 1957, pg. 15 reads: "Young Fry Step Out in Colorful Fashion Show! - Charlene and Toni Daniels - Portions of accompanying article reads: "Some of Pittsburgh's most delightful younger set members set a fast pace of fashions at the A. Leo Weil School Friday night, when the Centre Avenue Community Club presented a happy revue, complete with a singing, dancing prelude to styles..."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Charlene Daniels and Toni Daniels wearing identical light colored dresses with lace stripes around skirt, standing on stage in A. Leo Weil school for Community Club sponsored Fashion Show
